column5: Let me see... May, June, September, Early October, February, March..  Basically all times the general population is absent ! LOL
you are one lucky man irish.....thats all i have to say about that......
Oh... and some nice looking creatures come out thru July and August as well Robert !

well wayne i doubt if your talking about me. lol  we usually stop at the gas station to stretch our legs a little on our way up to elk lake at the end of july.  the scenery is usually Pretty good, and its nice little town as well.  jason
See above.. is your wife with you to qualify?
nope, just the guys, and their uglier than me.  jason
Been there July and September. But so far september is losing, it was damn cold in that tent -1 at night!

hey dan ive seen snow june 1st and cold ....left home with sun and reached temagami with wet snow and wind...still no better feeling than being there snow sun or rain its all good as long as your with good buddies and temagami.....

I love the winter in the Temagami area. We generally spend a week at Doug Adams place and hit two or three different lakes a day, a cornacopia of different species. It incredibly beautiful and Ive always been rewarded with lots of fish.

any time in temaagmi is heaven , would nt trade any time in the world for my time there wish i was still working on the lake, caught a 10 lb yrs ago june 6 5 pm skidoo suit and snowing heavily over 20 yrs ago in kokoko bay

musky or specks nice to see another winter fisherman.....malcom you are right all seasons are good as long as your in temagami...24 more days for me and ill be there cant wait it feels so far away.... some of the fishing buddies who will be joining me...except for (pops) the older gentleman he is gone fishing in heven..i learned alot from him...hes not my pops but treated me like one...i know heaven is just like temagami

musky or specks nice to see another winter fisherman.....malcom you are right all seasons are good as long as your in temagami...24 more days for me and ill be there cant wait it feels so far away.... some of the fishing buddies who will be joining me...except for (pops) the older gentleman he is gone fishing in heven..i learned alot from him...hes not my pops but treated me like one...i know heaven is just like temagami
Must be getting old Rob... you're starting to repeat yourself like my mother ! lol  6 days.....
hey wayne...they say the mind is the second thing to go......on men that is...lol here are the boys....
wayne you are so lucky you must be getting excited...what are you gonna fish for first...walleye...lakers...pike....ill be thinkin of ya when your there...will you be back before i leave...

Can't fish for anything unless I go into a back lake for specks. MNR went and played with the seasons so can't even fish for pike for the week 'till lakers open.  Other than one quick trip back to pick up my "commuter" vehicle ...Hopefully I'm not coming back until Sept 26th so I have a day to pack for Dano and I's trip to Montreal on the 28th. Pulling my hair out trying to get everything done...finished last customers airplane today....bills paid in advance..funds in place for the "kids" (20 to 25) to take care of anything else that comes up...got some lawn cutting equipment to service yet and a ton of other things...but I'll be there Sunday night or Monday am hell or high water.
wayne the "MACHINE" holy smokes i got tired just reading that
Fished Temagami for thirty years +. I love the ice-fishing the best. Still learning, still fishing. Would not trade it for the world.
